description:
&lt;p&gt;The ED team at Royal Blackburn are looking to recruit Band 5 staff nurses to join our busy team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a very busy department, covering a very diverse population, and we are also a major trauma unit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for self-motivated nurses to help take the department forward – you must be committed, flexible and approachable&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have a team of ENP’s, NP’s, ANP’s, Practice Educators and Nurse Consultant, supported by a diverse and innovative senior nursing team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We value all the different experiences and qualities people can bring to our department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a rotational post and covers all areas of the department, ED majors, Resus, UCC, paediatrics and also the UCC at Burnley and MIU at Accrington Victoria.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The department welcomes new members of staff and has an open and friendly culture which is strongly supportive of nursing development and expansion of skills. You will have a suitable period of supernumerary in which you will be supported by a mentor.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This job advert will close as soon as sufficient applications have been received. Please apply for this job as soon as you can, if interested. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Jacqueline Murray Matron - 01254 734706&lt;/p&gt;
